Frequently Asked Questions for Mueller Water Products (NYSE:MWA)
What is Mueller Water Products' stock symbol?

Mueller Water Products trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "MWA."



How often does Mueller Water Products pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Mueller Water Products?

Mueller Water Products announced a quarterly dividend on Thursday, April 20th. Shareholders of record on Wednesday, May 10th will be paid a dividend of $0.04 per share on Monday, May 22nd. This represents a $0.16 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.40%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Monday, May 8th.  View Mueller Water Products' Dividend History.



How will Mueller Water Products' stock buyback program work?

Mueller Water Products declared that its board has approved a share buyback program on Tuesday, April 11th 2017, which authorizes the company to repurchase $250,000,000.00 in    shares, according to EventVestor. This repurchase authorization authorizes the company to repurchase up to 128% of its stock  through open market purchases. Stock  repurchase programs are typically a sign that the company's management believes its shares are undervalued. 



How were Mueller Water Products' earnings last quarter?

Mueller Water Products (NYSE:MWA) posted its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April, 27th. The company reported $0.09 earnings per share for the quarter, hitting the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.09. The company had revenue of $199.70 million for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $206 million. Mueller Water Products had a return on equity of 18.45% and a net margin of 12.45%. The firm's revenue was up 1.3% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter in the prior year, the company posted $0.10 EPS.  View Mueller Water Products' Earnings History.



When will Mueller Water Products make its next earnings announcement?

Mueller Water Products is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Thursday, August, 3rd 2017. View Earnings Estimates for Mueller Water Products.



Where is Mueller Water Products' stock going? Where will Mueller Water Products' stock price be in 2017?

7 brokerages have issued 12 month target prices for Mueller Water Products' stock. Their forecasts range from $12.00 to $15.00. On average, they expect Mueller Water Products' stock price to reach $13.83 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Mueller Water Products.



Who are some of Mueller Water Products' key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Mueller Water Products include IMI plc (IMI), Barnes Group (B), KLX (KLXI), Manitowoc Food Service (WBT), Rexnord Corporation (RXN), Hillenbrand (HI), Proto Labs (PRLB), SPX FLOW (FLOW), Actuant Corporation (ATU), Kaman Corporation (KAMN), Comfort Systems USA (FIX), Milacron Holdings Corp. (MCRN), SPX Corporation (SPXC), SPX Corp (SPXC), American Outdoor Brands Corporation (AOBC), Hill & Smith Holdings PLC (HILS), Morgan Advanced Materials PLC (MGAM) and Park-Ohio Holdings Corp. (PKOH).



