Citadel Advisors LLC Takes Position in Milacron Holdings Corp. (NYSE:MCRN)

					Posted by James Quigley on Jul 10th, 2017 // No Comments 



Citadel Advisors LLC purchased a new stake in  Milacron Holdings Corp. (NYSE:MCRN) during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The fund purchased 165,633 shares of the industrial products company’s stock, valued at approximately $3,083,000. Citadel Advisors LLC owned 0.24% of Milacron Holdings Corp. at the end of the most recent quarter. 
Several other hedge funds have also recently modified their holdings of MCRN. Victory Capital Management Inc. purchased a new stake in shares of  Milacron Holdings Corp. during the first quarter valued at approximately $106,000.  Bronfman E.L. Rothschild L.P. boosted its stake in shares of  Milacron Holdings Corp. by 5.0% in the first quarter. Bronfman E.L. Rothschild L.P. now owns 6,297 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $117,000 after buying an additional 300 shares during the last quarter.  American International Group Inc. boosted its stake in shares of  Milacron Holdings Corp. by 7.0% in the first quarter. American International Group Inc. now owns 8,950 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $167,000 after buying an additional 588 shares during the last quarter.  Pitcairn Co. boosted its stake in shares of  Milacron Holdings Corp. by 7.0% in the first quarter. Pitcairn Co. now owns 12,840 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $239,000 after buying an additional 845 shares during the last quarter.  Finally, Two Sigma Investments LP purchased a new stake in shares of  Milacron Holdings Corp. during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $308,000. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  98.15% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Milacron Holdings Corp. alerts:



Shares of Milacron Holdings Corp. (NYSE MCRN) opened at 18.36 on Monday. Milacron Holdings Corp. has a one year low of $12.43 and a one year high of $19.45. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $17.89 and a 200 day moving average price of $18.10. The stock’s market capitalization is $1.27 billion. 




Milacron Holdings Corp. (NYSE:MCRN) last released its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The industrial products company reported $0.32 earnings per share for the quarter, hitting the consensus estimate of $0.32. The company had revenue of $285.40 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $270.31 million. Milacron Holdings Corp. had a negative return on equity of 52.73% and a negative net margin of 0.33%. Milacron Holdings Corp.’s revenue was up 2.9% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same quarter last year, the business posted $0.27 earnings per share.  On average, equities analysts expect that  Milacron Holdings Corp. will post $1.60 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
WARNING: “Citadel Advisors LLC Takes Position in Milacron Holdings Corp. (NYSE:MCRN)” was originally  reported by Transcript Daily and is owned by of Transcript Daily. If you are viewing this piece on another site, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of US & international copyright & trademark law. The correct version of this piece can be accessed at https://transcriptdaily.com/2017/07/10/citadel-advisors-llc-invests-3-08-million-in-milacron-holdings-corp-mcrn-updated-updated.html. 
Several brokerages have issued reports on MCRN. Zacks Investment Research upgraded Milacron Holdings Corp. from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $20.00 target price for the company in a report on Saturday, July 1st. BidaskClub cut Milacron Holdings Corp. from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a report on Friday, June 23rd. Finally, Robert W. Baird  set a $23.00 target price on Milacron Holdings Corp. and gave the company a “buy” rating in a report on Wednesday, May 17th.
In other Milacron Holdings Corp. news, Director James Gentilcore sold 15,000 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction on Wednesday, June 14th. The stock was sold at an average price of $19.14, for a total transaction of $287,100.00. The transaction was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this hyperlink. Also, Director Ira G. Boots sold 2,500 shares of the firm’s stock in a transaction on Monday, May 1st. The stock was sold at an average price of $18.37, for a total value of $45,925.00. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders have sold 23,316,086 shares of company stock valued at $385,240,919 in the last three months. 3.40% of the stock is currently owned by company insiders. 
About Milacron Holdings Corp.
Milacron Holdings Corp. is engaged in the manufacture, distribution, and service of engineered and customized systems used in the plastic technology and processing industry. The Company operates through three segments: Advanced Plastic Processing Technologies (APPT), Melt Delivery and Control Systems (MDCS), and Fluid Technologies.







