Citadel Advisors LLC Invests $109,000 in Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (AVAL)

					Posted by Brenda Bartman on Jul 20th, 2017 // No Comments 



Citadel Advisors LLC bought a new stake in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (NYSE:AVAL) during the first quarter, according to its most recent Form 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The fund bought 13,371 shares of the bank’s stock, valued at approximately $109,000. 
Other institutional investors also recently added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Guggenheim Capital LLC increased its position in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores by 41.6% in the fourth quarter. Guggenheim Capital LLC now owns 88,343 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $701,000 after buying an additional 25,956 shares during the last quarter.  Brandes Investment Partners LP increased its position in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores by 0.3% in the first quarter. Brandes Investment Partners LP now owns 7,690,216 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $65,852,000 after buying an additional 22,135 shares during the last quarter.  Findlay Park Partners LLP increased its position in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores by 10.4% in the first quarter. Findlay Park Partners LLP now owns 1,613,698 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $13,182,000 after buying an additional 152,310 shares during the last quarter.  Allianz Asset Management AG acquired a new position in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores during the fourth quarter valued at approximately $556,000.  Finally, Stevens Capital Management LP acquired a new position in shares of  Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores during the first quarter valued at approximately $126,000. Institutional investors own  21.98% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. alerts:



Shares of Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. (NYSE:AVAL) traded down 0.92% during midday trading on Thursday, hitting $8.59. The stock had a trading volume of 51,912 shares. The firm has a 50 day moving average price of $8.35 and a 200-day moving average price of $8.18. Grupo Aval Acciones y Valores S.A. has a 52-week low of $7.18 and a 52-week high of $9.04. The stock has a market cap of $9.57 billion, a PE ratio of 13.85 and a beta of 0.53. 




