Frequently Asked Questions for Mueller Industries (NYSE:MLI)
What is Mueller Industries' stock symbol?

Mueller Industries trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "MLI."



How often does Mueller Industries pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Mueller Industries?

Mueller Industries announced a quarterly dividend on Monday, May 8th. Stockholders of record on Friday, June 2nd will be paid a dividend of $0.10 per share on Friday, June 16th. This represents a $0.40 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.30%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, May 31st.  View Mueller Industries' Dividend History.



When did Mueller Industries' stock split? How did Mueller Industries' stock split work?

Mueller Industries's stock  split on Monday, March 31st 2014. The 2-1 split was announced on Friday, February 21st 2014. The newly created shares were payable to shareholders after the closing bell on Friday, March 28th 2014. An investor that had 100 shares of Mueller Industries stock prior to the split would have 200 shares after the split.



How were Mueller Industries' earnings last quarter?

Mueller Industries, Inc. (NYSE:MLI) released its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, April, 25th. The company reported $0.52 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter. The firm earned $577.92 million during the quarter. Mueller Industries had a net margin of 4.65% and a return on equity of 13.99%.  View Mueller Industries' Earnings History.



Who are some of Mueller Industries' key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Mueller Industries include Worthington Industries (WOR), Belden (BDC), Barnes Group (B), Kennametal (KMT), Enersys (ENS), MSA Safety Incorporporated (MSA), John Bean Technologies Corporation (JBT), Aggreko PLC (ARGKF), Unifirst Corporation (UNF), Cimpress N.V (CMPR), Greif Bros. Corporation (GEF), Tetra Tech (TTEK), Manitowoc Food Service (WBT), RBC Bearings Incorporated (ROLL), II-VI Incorporated (IIVI), Rexnord Corporation (RXN), iRobot Corporation (IRBT) and Applied Industrial Technologies (AIT).



